Sentencas: The microstructure and interfacial property of a thin film electrolyte solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) were investigated using transmission electron microscopy (TEM).
Titulo: Transmission Electron Microscopy Study on Microstructure and Interfacial Property of Thin Film Electrolyte SOFC

Sentencas: The NiO-yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) nanocomposite layer, the electrolyte, and the cathode layers were fabricated by using pulsed laser deposition and exhibited various microstructures such as a dense microstructure with equiaxed grains, a dense microstructure with columnar grains, and a nanoporous and granular microstructure, depending on their material, deposition condition, and deposition surface.
Titulo: Transmission Electron Microscopy Study on Microstructure and Interfacial Property of Thin Film Electrolyte SOFC

Sentencas: In addition, the TEM analysis revealed that the reaction buffer to suppress the chemical reaction of lanthanum strontium cobaltite and YSZ is required even for the low temperature fabrication and operation (<= 650 degrees C).
Titulo: Transmission Electron Microscopy Study on Microstructure and Interfacial Property of Thin Film Electrolyte SOFC
